

Kubernetes Deployment & Service for Python App (from Docker Hub)
— written in the same simple style so you can run without errors.

✅ 🔹 OVERVIEW (What you are doing)
You will:

Pull a Python app image from Docker Hub
Deploy it in Kubernetes using YAML
Run multiple replicas
Expose it using a Service
Access it in browser
🔹 Step 0: Prerequisites
Install & start:

Docker Desktop
Minikube
kubectl
🔹 Step 1: Start Kubernetes Cluster
minikube start --driver=docker
🔹 Step 2: Verify Cluster
kubectl get nodes
✅ Output:

Ready
🔹 Step 3: Pull Python App Image
We use Docker Hub sample:

docker pull dockersamples/flaskapp
✔ Confirms image is available

🔹 Step 4: Create Deployment YAML
Create file:

python-deployment.yaml
Paste:

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: python-web-deployment
  labels:
    app: python-web

spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: python-web

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: python-web

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: python-web
        image: dockersamples/flaskapp:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
🔹 Step 5: Apply Deployment
kubectl apply -f python-deployment.yaml
🔹 Step 6: Check Deployment
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods
✅ Expected:

2 pods running
🔹 Step 7: View Details (Optional)
kubectl describe deployment python-web-deployment
🔹 Step 8: Create Service YAML
Create file:

python-service.yaml
Paste:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: python-web-service

spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: python-web

  ports:
  - protocol: TCP
    port: 5000
    targetPort: 5000
🔹 Step 9: Apply Service
kubectl apply -f python-service.yaml
🔹 Step 10: Check Service
kubectl get svc
🔹 Step 11: Get Application URL
minikube service python-web-service --url
👉 Open the URL in browser

✅ You will see:
👉 Python Flask Web App Page

🔹 Step 12: Cleanup
Delete resources:

kubectl delete -f python-deployment.yaml
kubectl delete -f python-service.yaml
🔹 Step 13: Stop Cluster
minikube stop
(Optional)

minikube delete
🔥 Common Errors (IMPORTANT)
❌ Pods not running
✔ Check:

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
❌ Image not pulling
✔ Ensure internet OR run:

docker pull dockersamples/flaskapp
❌ Service not opening
✔ Run again:

minikube service python-web-service --url
❌ Port issue
✔ Minikube auto handles NodePort → no need to change

🧠 Viva Short Answers
👉 What is Deployment?
Manages pods and replicas.

👉 What is Service?
Exposes app to outside network.

👉 Why replicas = 2?
For scalability and high availability.

👉 What is NodePort?
Exposes app on a port accessible outside cluster.

👉 What is Docker Hub?
Repository for container images.

